<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-278-312  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 278 312.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  March 26 1990 n460 p30(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Resellers change course. (process manufacturing)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rosenhouse, Helene.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Value-added resellers are now concentrating their applicationsoftware efforts on process manufacturing instead of the discretemanufacturing arena.andP;  Process manufacturers have previouslyfocused on automating plant control functions while discretemanufacturers, whose products have a high engineering content,were automating management functions such as inventory control andfinancial planning.andP;  The shift to process manufacturingapplications is spurred by increasing global competition, productproliferation, shorter product cycles and stricter US regulations.andO;Industry analysts estimate that the process industry will spendfrom 15- to 20 percent more in 1990 on computer automationproducts while the discrete manufacturers automation market willgrow by only five to seven percent.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Value-Added Resellersm Market ShareManufacturingOffice Automation SoftwareProcess ManagementTrends.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraphtable.andO;Caption:   Floor models: growth of shop floor market. (graph)Growth process: automation spending increases. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>